President Barack Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. These include Luis G. Hoyos as a member of the Advisory Council on Historic Preservation, Jackie Richter-Menge as a member of the Arctic Research Commission, James G. Featherstone as a member of the Medal of Valor Review Board, George S. Hawkins as a member of the National Infrastructure Advisory Council, Laurence M. Baer as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council, and Eric A. LeVine as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. President Obama expressed his pleasure in having these experienced individuals serve the country.